      "notes": "Guest dinner (Rhodes + Hernandez), 6 people (~2 racks; others bringing food). NO SMOKER NEEDED — gas-grill two-zone: light one burner, ribs on the unlit side, lid down, hold ~225°F; smoke with a foil pouch of wood chips (4 oz, re-add once, then stop after the first hour). Baby backs ~3-4 h; done by the bend test. Dry-brine (kosher salt ~1/2 tsp/lb) up to 12 h ahead, then the salt-free Memphis Dust. Sauce only in the last 15-30 min. Rub can go on up to 3 days ahead; make the Memphis Dust batch anytime (keeps months).",
